  "text": "Although CAT2 is induced in certain murine models of asthma and mediators released from eosinophils can inhibit the function of CAT [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , the expression of CAT2 and CAT1 proteins has not been examined in human asthma. Uptake of L-arginine by CAT is critical to L-arginine bioavailability within the cell. Inasmuch as expression of ARG1 was significantly upregulated in the lung specimens from asthma patients compared with nonasthmatic controls, in the absence of augmented expression of CAT1 or CAT2, our results support the potential for decreased intracellular bioavailability of L-arginine for NOS in asthmatic airways.",
